Wash and dry produce.

Halve @lime{1}. Trim and halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise
into half-moons. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

== Pickled Cucumber ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (you'll use
the rest later), juice from half the lime, @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4
servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Stir in cucumber. Set aside to quick-pickle.

== Beef and Carrots ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick,
#pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce} and cook,
stirring, until just tender, ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
@ground beef{10%ounce}; season with a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, breaking
up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon} and remaining vinegar. Bring to a
simmer, then immediately turn off heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

== Sriracha Mayo ==

In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}
to taste. Season with salt. Stir in @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Assembly ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with saucy beef, carrots, pickled
cucumber (draining first), and cilantro. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo. Cut
remaining lime into wedges and serve on the side.